The SANBS has made an urgent national call upon all its regular and new donors to stand together and help bolster the country&#8217;s O-type blood supply level which currently stands at less than 1 500 available units.SANBS Limpopo Media Relations Officer Dottie Pinn said Limpopo&#8217;s levels for all blood types are currently at 1,1 days available stock. She has urged the community to visit the SANBS offices in Potgieter Avenue to help relief the shortage. Story: THINUS DU TOIT &gt;&gt;thinus@observer.co.za &nbsp;